==English==
===Etymology===
From French, from Latin '''[[admiratio]]''', from prefix '''[[ad-]]''', ''to'', + '''[[mirare]]''', '''"look at"''', + noun of action suffix '''[[-tio]]'''.
See '''[[admire]]'''.

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˌæd.mɚˈeɪ.ʃən/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʃǝn|-eɪʃǝn]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
#[[Wonder]] [[mingle]]d with [[approbation]] or [[delight]]; an [[emotion]] [[excited]] by a person or thing possessed of [[wonderful]] or high [[excellence]]; as, admiration of a beautiful woman, of a landscape, of virtue.

====Synonyms====
[[Wonder]]; [[approval]]; [[appreciation]]; [[adoration]]; [[reverence]]; [[worship]].

====Derived terms====
*[[admirative]]
*[[admiratively]]

